This was excellent. I took most cooks' advice -- from adding grated carrots, red wine, and sliced mushrooms to using a half pound of mixed hot and sweet Italian sausage -- and it turned out scrumptious. A couple of improvements I'd suggest: Don't put all of the sauce on all of the pasta. There's enough for two to three meals here, and you'll end up having to bake or microwave the leftovers. For a fresher taste, I'd prefer to dip the noodles in boiling water and to simply reheat the sauce. And, true, as one reviewer pointed out, this dish is meat-heavy...but the sausage adds exquisite flavor and it all blends well. Due to the large amount of sauce produced, I'd recommend making this with 1.5 pounds of spaghetti.

