To the cook from Winnipeg: I have prepared cocktail size meatballs, baked in 350 oven for 15 minutes. I cool, place on cookie sheets & freeze. Then I put them in a bag/container & can take out as many as I want for whatever. For spaghetti, you might want the meatballs larger. If so, bake 20-25 minutes. I would also freeze some of the pan drippings to add to the sauce for flavor.

