Amazing flavor and texture. I heeded the warnings about combining the bread and I think this process may help everyone. I first combined the egg, cheese, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic in my electric mixer. Then, I added the bread and mixed it on high for about 20 seconds. This pretty much pulverizes the bread. Finally, I added the meat and mixed on medium high for 30 seconds. The mixture was very uniform and the end result was a very moist and flavorful meatball.

