Rating: 3
I thought these were great - I'd note a couple things: 1) break up the bread very well before combining with the other ingredients. I combined everything in the bowl right after squeezing the bread dry, and ended up with squashy and sort of unappealing chunks of soft bread in the cooked meatballs because I was afraid I'd overhandle the mixture if I tried too hard to break the bread up while mixing. Distributing the bread more evenly would have helped it be more of a binder as well - my meatballs were a little crumbly (but no less tasty for that). 2) Cooking these in the oven was a huge plus: no grease splattering on the stove, and a great browned exterior with no added fat. Pop in a rimmed baking sheet and bake in a preheated 350 oven for 20-30 minutes or so, shaking occasionally.

