Rating: 0
I was just going through some recipes and saw this and though I didn't make it...it's very authentic. My husband is from Naples and we have gone there several times and the meatballs are pretty much how they make them there. The sauce is pretty authentic, too. It's called a ragu` in Italy and also includes braciola. Try adding some red wine before adding the tomatoes and fry up the meatballs in the same pot as the sausage. Also, I don't use bread soaked in milk, I cheat and use plain dried bread crumbs, and the meatballs are still moist and delish...try it.Also, the Italians NEVER eat a ragu` with spaghetti, it's always eaten with rigatoni or ziti. It was news to this Irish girl, too.

