Great recipe, but not one that I would try again in the shape that it currently is. I don't know if the Italians originally planned all their food bland and lifeless, but it certainly seems to have become the norm these days. Spice it up! Add some flavor! Give it some life! When I last made this, the people I were entertaining did not like the 'raw' taste of meat, so I made the meatballs 3/4 of meat and 1/4 of freshly mashed potatoes and garlic. This really made the meatballs plump, tender, and they held together marvellously without losing out any on flavor. I totally agree with the fact that the dish tastes better if you let it sit in the fridge overnight. When you take it out, theres less sauce and its thicker, so what I did is to flesh it out again with a dash of red wine while reheating! C'est incroyable!! Do try it, its not 'proper' but it leads to a very tasty dish!

