My family really enjoyed this classic dinner dish. I used a small cookie scoop to scoop the meat mixture onto a cookie cooling rack. I rounded up the edges, put the rack on top of a cookie sheet and baked at 350 for 20 minutes. It works everytime! Fast and not much grease. I also use this technique for Swedish meatballs.

