Rating: 2
Instead of using 1 pound of ground sirloin, use 1/2 pound ground sirloin and then 1/4 pound of ground pork and 1/2 pound of ground veal. At every butcher and some grocery stores too if you ask. Not joking - the meatballs will be SO MUCH BETTER. And to the cook that had the problem with the meatballs falling apart in the pan, this meat mix will definitely help with that. And also, before you put each one in the oil, wet your hands a little and drop them in. Works for me and has worked for my 85 year old grandmother her whole life!

